<!DOCTYPE html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <title> Color Game </title>
    <meta name="description" content="">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="app.css">
</head>

<body>
    <div> <a href="/highscores"> High Scores</a></div>
    <h1> Daniel's <br> <span id="RGB"> RGB </span> <br> Color Game </h1>
    <div id="gameBar">
        <span id="round" class=""> Round: <span class="roundNum">1</span></span>
        <span id="timer" class=""> Time Remaining: <span id="time">10</span>s
            <button id="gamePauseButton" class="invisible">Pause</button></span>


        <span id="message" class=""></span>
        <span id="score" class=""> Score: <span class="scoreNum"></span></span>
        <span id="lives" class=""> Lives Left: <span id="livesNum"></span></span>
        <!-- <span><button class="mode" id="easy">Easy</button><button id="hard" class="mode selected">Hard</button></span> -->
    </div>

    <div id="gameContainer" class="container invisible">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="square"></div>
            <div class="square"></div>
            <div class="square"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="square"></div>
            <div class="square"></div>
            <div class="square"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div id="preGame" class="container">
        <div id="instructions">
            <p> What is RGB? </p>
            <p> The RGB color model is an additive color model in which red, green, and blue light are added together in
                various ways to reproduce a broad array of colors. Each parameter (red, green, and blue) defines the
                intensity of the color as an integer between 0 and 255. For example, rgb(0, 0, 255) is rendered as blue,
                because the blue parameter is set to its highest value (255) and the others are set to 0.
            <p> How to Play? </p>
            <p>
                <!-- The idea of the game is to guess the correct square that indicates the RGB color that will show in the
                    header. -->
                When you start the round you will have 3 seconds to study the RGB color at the top of the
                page. Then, six squares of different colors will appear and you will have to guess the correct square
                that indicates the RGB color.
                Each round has a 10 second countdown so the quicker you guess, the more points you will receive.
                However, be
                careful, if
                you guess wrong (or don't decide before the timer runs out), you lose a life! How many rounds can you
                survive? How many points can you score? Time to find out...
            </p>
            <p> Ready to Play? </p>
        </div>
        <div class="startGameButtonDiv">
            <button class="startGameButton"> Start Game </button>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div id="preRound" class="invisible">
        <div class="startGameButtonDiv container">
            <div> Once you click the start round button you will have 3 seconds to study the next round's RGB color in
                the header above</div>
            <div><button id="startRoundButton"> Start Round <span class="roundNum"></span> </button></div>
            <div id="roundCountdownDiv" class="container invisible">Round <span class="roundNum"></span> starting in...
                <span id="roundCountdownDivNumber"></span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div id="postGameModal" class="modal container invisible">
        <!-- Modal content -->
        <div class="modal-content">
            <h4> Game Over! </h4>
            <!-- <span class="modal-close">&times;</span> -->
            <p>
                <div> Round: <span class="roundNum"> </span> </div>
                <div> Score: <span class="scoreNum"> </span> </div>
            </p>
           
            <p> 
                <form action="/highscores" method="POST">
                    <input type="text" name="highscore[name]" placeholder="Name"> 
                    <input id="finalScore" type="hidden" name="highscore[score]" > 
                    <input id="finalRound" type="hidden" name="highscore[round]" > 
                    <button> Submit </button>
                </form>
            </p>
          
            <button class="startGameButton"> Play Again? </button>
         
           
        
          
        </div>

    </div>

    <script id="jsFile" src="logic.js" data="<% min_highscore %>"async defer></script>
</body>

</html>